Durban - A decision on the bail application of the 11 suspects allegedly linked to the bomb attacks in Durban is expected to be delivered in the Verulam Magistrate's Court today. The suspects face charges of terrorism, murder, attempted murder, extortion, kidnapping, contravention of the Explosives Act and arson. In October 19 men were arrested. Charges against 7 of the accused were provisionally withdrawn while Goolam Haffajee, 38, was released on R100 000 bail on October 15. The 11 accused are being held at Westville prison. The men are allegedly linked tolinked to the attack on the Imam Hussein Mosque in Verulam in May where Abbas Essop was killed. The suspects arrests were made by an integrated team involving the Hawks (Crimes Against the State), Crime Intelligence, the Forensic Unit, the National Prosecuting Authority including other departments from the justice cluster. Wealthy businessman Farhad Hoomer, 42, from AshervilleÂ has been fingered as the ringleader. According to East Coast Radio the trial is only expected to start in 2020 and would conclude a year later. Daily News 